Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a pottery transport amphora. Clay fine mid red-brown; cream slip. Circular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 101a, 5 ( a more probably identification than the less well preserved 2011,5003.440, from the same die. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1642)
